sentences: Younghi Pagh-Paan (born 1945) is a South Korean composer.
She studied music at the Seoul National University from 1965–71.

In 1974 she received a DAAD scholarship to study in Germany and entered the Freiburg Musikhochschule, where she studied composition with Klaus Huber, analysis with Brian Ferneyhough, music theory with Peter Förtig and piano with Edith Picht-Axenfeld.
After completing her studies, she took guest professorships at Graz in 1991 and Karlsruhe in 1992–93.
After completing her studies, she took guest professorships at Graz in 1991 and Karlsruhe in 1992–93.
In 1994 she became a professor of composition at the University of the Arts Bremen.
She was one of the top 10 performed composers on the Internationalen Ferienkurse für Neue Musik between 1946 and 2014.
1985 Scholarship from the Kunststiftung of Baden-Württemberg
2006 Lifetime Achievement Award of Seoul National University
2007 Order of Civil Merit of the Republic of Korea (South Korea)
2009 Member of the Akademie der Künste, Berlin
